             depos'd, He saw him take off Pridgeon's Hat and Wig, but what Money they took from him he could not tell; he added, they took from him 4 s. 6 d. and they had unbutton'd his Clothes, in order to strip him , but he took an opportunity to slip from them; but the Prisoner took his Hat, and struck him. The Facts being plainly prov'd, and the Prisoner not denying it, the Jury found him <rs id="t17300408-65-verdict332" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17300408-65-verdict332" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
