               Death
            </rs> .</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="173004080017"></xptr>The Prisoner pleaded, that he had been admitted an Evidence, and had convicted Frier and Ferdinando Srimpton of Murder, and had put this very Fact in his Information, and therefore thought his Case hard to be try'd for this Fact; whereupon the Court intimated , that his Case should be favourably represented to His Majesty.</p>
